00:56:58.240 --> 00:57:04.320
your subtle energy system is running more&nbsp;
powerfully than it had run previously.&nbsp;

00:57:04.320 --> 00:57:12.480
And this energy is contagious. States of&nbsp;
consciousness are contagious. Negative states&nbsp;

00:57:12.480 --> 00:57:19.680
are contagious. Positive states are contagious.&nbsp;
And it's just a natural fact of nature. So my&nbsp;

00:57:19.680 --> 00:57:25.200
energy was triggering their energy. Now,&nbsp;
most people were not activated in this way,&nbsp;

00:57:25.200 --> 00:57:31.280
but those who were receptive were activated.&nbsp;
And then I imagine it fed back to you and&nbsp;

00:57:31.920 --> 00:57:37.040
influenced you yet again. Yeah. And so there&nbsp;
was often a feedback loop that would happen.&nbsp;

00:57:37.040 --> 00:57:42.480
I would say something, it would open up them.&nbsp;
They would more energy come into the room. I&nbsp;

00:57:42.480 --> 00:57:48.400
would receive it. It would affect me. Sometimes&nbsp;
there was so much creativity in the room that&nbsp;

00:57:48.400 --> 00:57:53.680
after the class was over, I would copy down&nbsp;
the blackboard because I had gotten insights&nbsp;

00:57:53.680 --> 00:57:59.440
and seen things that I had not seen as&nbsp;
clearly, quite as clearly, before that time.&nbsp;

00:57:59.440 --> 00:58:07.760
Now, I've used LSD a lot myself, and probably&nbsp;
over a hundred times. Not as methodically as&nbsp;

00:58:07.760 --> 00:58:15.840
you have done, but still with the intent of doing&nbsp;
it for self-awareness and spiritual purposes.&nbsp;

00:58:15.840 --> 00:58:26.400
And it's led me to be where I am today, I&nbsp;
suppose. I have no regrets whatsoever. But&nbsp;

00:58:26.400 --> 00:58:33.120
it can be a little bit debilitating. A heavy&nbsp;
dose of LSD leaves one, like the next day,&nbsp;

00:58:33.120 --> 00:58:39.920
kind of exhausted. Exhausted, yeah. When&nbsp;
you open in those deep states, you open&nbsp;

00:58:39.920 --> 00:58:44.480
into very high energy levels of awareness.&nbsp;
And I learned that every deeper level of&nbsp;

00:58:44.480 --> 00:58:49.360
consciousness functions at a higher level of&nbsp;
energy. So when you go into those deep levels,&nbsp;

00:58:49.360 --> 00:58:55.920
you're opening into high energy. And after it's&nbsp;
all over, you can feel tired. Your subtle energy&nbsp;

00:58:55.920 --> 00:59:04.800
system can feel achy. And the more I began to&nbsp;
appreciate the cost of each session to your body,&nbsp;

00:59:05.360 --> 00:59:11.600
the more I began to prepare more conscientiously&nbsp;
for each session. So I would do certain spiritual&nbsp;

00:59:11.600 --> 00:59:18.320
practices before session, and then deeper,&nbsp;
different practices, soul integration practices&nbsp;

00:59:18.320 --> 00:59:23.680
after a session. I would make sure I would have&nbsp;
a chiropractic adjustment and a massage before&nbsp;

00:59:23.680 --> 00:59:28.800
session, because I wanted my system to be&nbsp;
as balanced and open as possible to handle&nbsp;

00:59:28.800 --> 00:59:36.480
what was about to happen. But it does. It takes&nbsp;
days. I find that there's a 24-hour window,&nbsp;

00:59:36.480 --> 00:59:42.880
then there's kind of a three-day window, about&nbsp;
a 10-day window, and a one-month window. And it&nbsp;

00:59:42.880 --> 00:59:49.200
closes gradually. And that's one of the things I&nbsp;
emphasize if you're working systematically with&nbsp;

00:59:49.200 --> 00:59:55.120
psychedelics, to have a daily spiritual practice.&nbsp;
And the deeper you're working with psychedelics,&nbsp;

00:59:55.120 --> 01:00:00.480
the more important it is to have a daily&nbsp;
spiritual practice, because it helps you stabilize&nbsp;

01:00:00.480 --> 01:00:07.200
what opens you in those experiences, stabilize&nbsp;
it, and also helps you process the enormous energy&nbsp;

01:00:07.200 --> 01:00:12.800
that otherwise would build up in my body. And&nbsp;
by doing spiritual practice and meditation,&nbsp;

01:00:12.800 --> 01:00:19.600
it gave that energy a place to run in between&nbsp;
sessions. So it is challenging. It takes time.&nbsp;

01:00:19.600 --> 01:00:28.480
It's not to be taken lightly. Have you looked into&nbsp;
the physiological aspects of LSD, how it might&nbsp;

01:00:28.480 --> 01:00:31.920
work? I know there are different&nbsp;
theories. Does it activate the&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:00:31.920 --> 01:00:37.920
brain to push you into a higher level,
or is it the opposite? Does it deactivate or&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:00:37.920 --> 01:00:43.760
activate some parts and deactivate other parts?
Yeah, the default turning off the default mode&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:00:43.760 --> 01:00:48.960
network and opening up. You know, I pay attention
to that. And I try to follow it. I'm not a&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:00:48.960 --> 01:00:56.240
scientist, so I don't pretend to be a scientist.
But for the most part, I let the science guys&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:00:56.240 --> 01:01:00.960
work out, hold on to those&nbsp;
details. And I find that when&nbsp;

01:01:00.960 --> 01:01:06.960
they are interpreting the physiological data that&nbsp;
they get, they usually are working it within some&nbsp;

01:01:06.960 --> 01:01:12.160
set of metaphysical assumptions. And some of those&nbsp;
metaphysical assumptions are more adequate than&nbsp;

01:01:12.160 --> 01:01:22.480
others. And my metaphysical experience is&nbsp;
rather extreme. And so some of that stuff&nbsp;

01:01:22.480 --> 01:01:30.080
doesn't seem to me to be getting at the core.&nbsp;
Some of it does. Shutting down the default mode&nbsp;

01:01:30.080 --> 01:01:36.400
network opens us up to greater creativity and&nbsp;
whatnot. But I think that much of that discussion&nbsp;

01:01:36.400 --> 01:01:46.400
still doesn't appreciate the depth of cosmological&nbsp;
access that opens in deep psychedelic experience.&nbsp;

01:01:46.400 --> 01:01:51.040
One of the problems I think in our history,&nbsp;
our intellectual history around psychedelics,&nbsp;

01:01:51.040 --> 01:02:00.240
is that many fundamental or influential accounts&nbsp;
were written after only a handful of experiences.&nbsp;

01:02:00.240 --> 01:02:07.440
So The Doors of Perception, Aldous Huxley, a&nbsp;
wonderful book after one experience. He was a&nbsp;

01:02:07.440 --> 01:02:12.640
great writer. He was a great writer and a great&nbsp;
thinker. When Houston Smith wrote Cleansing the&nbsp;

01:02:12.640 --> 01:02:17.600
Doors of Perception, which is his collection of&nbsp;
his writings on psychedelics, he had only taken&nbsp;

01:02:17.600 --> 01:02:24.080
LSD six times. And after that, he said the bummers&nbsp;
increased and he decided to hang up the phone,&nbsp;

01:02:24.080 --> 01:02:29.440
take out lots of experience. But that sort of&nbsp;
underestimates what can happen if you don't hang&nbsp;

01:02:29.440 --> 01:02:35.520
up the phone, if you keep going back to the well.&nbsp;
And when Michael Pollan wrote his book, a very&nbsp;

01:02:35.520 --> 01:02:42.080
important, helpful book, How to Change Your Mind,&nbsp;
he had only taken psychedelics a handful of times,&nbsp;

01:02:42.080 --> 01:02:45.520
which I think helps explain&nbsp;
some of the limitations of his&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:02:45.520 --> 01:02:51.600
interpretation of how psychedelics work that
come in the end of the book. I think it's&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:02:51.600 --> 01:02:58.880
important for us to not just look at the first
few experiences that open, but what opens in a&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:02:58.880 --> 01:03:05.200
long lineage of experiences. And here we have
a lot to learn from the indigenous cultures&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:03:05.200 --> 01:03:10.560
who have been working with psychedelics for
thousands of years, and they have a long lifetime&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:03:10.560 --> 01:03:18.240
of working with these states. And there are
advanced chapters that open in the book only&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:03:18.240 --> 01:03:25.920
after the preliminary chapters have been digested.
Well, I was about to say that I thought you&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:03:25.920 --> 01:03:35.840
probably identified yourself as a philosophical
idealist. Now I'm not so sure, because I don't&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:03:35.840 --> 01:03:44.640
think that indigenous cultures would necessarily
go along with that. Yeah, and you know, every&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:03:44.640 --> 01:03:50.080
psychedelic has a certain spectrum. It operates
on a certain spectrum of consciousness, from even&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:03:50.080 --> 01:03:57.280
low dose to high dose, but generally there's a
certain range that it activates. And I think LSD&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:03:57.280 --> 01:04:02.080
tends to, what I think of as kind of a high
altitude psychedelic, it tends to operate,&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:04:02.080 --> 01:04:07.520
activate at higher levels,&nbsp;
very high cosmological levels.&nbsp;

01:04:07.520 --> 01:04:12.240
Something like psilocybin, which is such a&nbsp;
wonderful psychedelic, which is so body-oriented&nbsp;

01:04:12.240 --> 01:04:19.280
and heart-oriented and emotionally oriented, it&nbsp;
tends to operate at a different level, a lower&nbsp;

01:04:19.280 --> 01:04:25.840
level in some ways, but a rich level. And so&nbsp;
we have to look at each particular psychedelic,&nbsp;

01:04:25.840 --> 01:04:32.000
the spectrum of consciousness that it activates,&nbsp;
how we can work with each one, and then we start&nbsp;

01:04:32.000 --> 01:04:37.440
to put the puzzle together. Does what we learn&nbsp;
from psilocybin, how does that mesh with what&nbsp;

01:04:37.440 --> 01:04:45.120
we learn from ayahuasca and LSD? Pretty soon we&nbsp;
start to have a larger landscape that's waiting&nbsp;

01:04:45.120 --> 01:04:54.160
for us in these states. Now I know you are on&nbsp;
the board of directors of the Grof Institute,&nbsp;

01:04:54.160 --> 01:04:58.560
isn't that correct? Yeah, I'm on&nbsp;
the advisory board of Grof Legacy&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:04:58.560 --> 01:05:02.880
Training. Yeah, I see myself very
much in Stan's lineage. I mean,&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:05:04.160 --> 01:05:09.600
he was the one whose books&nbsp;
gave me the confidence to go&nbsp;

01:05:09.600 --> 01:05:14.320
where I eventually went. And if I push the&nbsp;
boundaries of his paradigm a little bit here&nbsp;

01:05:14.320 --> 01:05:21.440
and there, I still feel myself very strongly&nbsp;
within his lineage. Well, if I understand it&nbsp;

01:05:21.440 --> 01:05:28.080
correctly, and I did know Stan quite well in&nbsp;
the days when I lived in California, did many&nbsp;

01:05:28.080 --> 01:05:40.160
interviews with him, I am under the impression&nbsp;
that his thrust was that there are ways to achieve&nbsp;

01:05:40.160 --> 01:05:47.600
psychedelic states through breathing exercises&nbsp;
and through other methods that don't involve&nbsp;

01:05:47.600 --> 01:05:53.840
molecules. Yeah, yeah, and he's done that and&nbsp;
demonstrated that in worldwide workshops and&nbsp;

01:05:53.840 --> 01:06:00.240
teachings. And you can't make breathing illegal.&nbsp;
And all you have to do is breathe deeply in a&nbsp;

01:06:00.960 --> 01:06:07.120
precise kind of way, and carefully control&nbsp;
circumstances, and you amplify consciousness,&nbsp;

01:06:07.120 --> 01:06:13.760
and the same mechanisms begin to be activated that&nbsp;
can be activated with a psychedelic substance.&nbsp;

01:06:13.760 --> 01:06:21.520
So to me, psychedelics are not to the point. It's&nbsp;
the nature of consciousness that is to the point.&nbsp;

01:06:21.520 --> 01:06:26.400
Psychedelics amplify consciousness, but it's&nbsp;
consciousness that does the work. And that's why&nbsp;

01:06:26.400 --> 01:06:33.200
there's a fundamental convergence of the vision of&nbsp;
reality that emerges in the great non-psychedelic&nbsp;

01:06:33.200 --> 01:06:38.320
spiritual contemplative traditions and the&nbsp;
psychedelic traditions. We're not discovering&nbsp;

01:06:38.320 --> 01:06:44.240
a new universe. We're discovering the same&nbsp;
universe using a different set of techniques&nbsp;

01:06:44.240 --> 01:06:52.480
to explore that universe. So, but I presume&nbsp;
you're not actively engaged in training holotropic&nbsp;

01:06:52.480 --> 01:07:02.240
therapy? No, I made a choice long ago not to&nbsp;
function clinically. I think that's a different&nbsp;

01:07:02.240 --> 01:07:07.440
set of skills. You require a different set of&nbsp;
training to when you work with other people,&nbsp;

01:07:07.440 --> 01:07:12.880
taking other people into these states. You have to&nbsp;
not only know what you're doing from having your&nbsp;

01:07:12.880 --> 01:07:18.160
own experiences in these states, but you should&nbsp;
have a good strong clinical grounding so you can&nbsp;

01:07:18.160 --> 01:07:24.880
recognize when things are not going well and how&nbsp;
to work with other people. I decided to function&nbsp;

01:07:24.880 --> 01:07:28.240
as an explorer, as a solitary explorer,&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:07:28.240 --> 01:07:32.080
to push the boundaries as far&nbsp;
as I could, and then to bring&nbsp;

01:07:32.080 --> 01:07:38.720
back and share what I had learned with other&nbsp;
people. And I find that people who respond to&nbsp;

01:07:38.720 --> 01:07:43.440
LSD in the Mind of the Universe, many of&nbsp;
them are psychedelic people themselves,&nbsp;

01:07:43.440 --> 01:07:49.600
but many of them are not. Many of them just have&nbsp;
a long lifelong practice in meditation or yoga&nbsp;

01:07:49.600 --> 01:07:54.720
and they recognize a parallel between what&nbsp;
they've experienced and what I'm describing.&nbsp;

01:07:54.720 --> 01:07:59.200
I think that's really important. It's&nbsp;
consciousness that does the work.&nbsp;

01:07:59.200 --> 01:08:06.000
Well, I totally agree with you about that.&nbsp;
I guess that's the main thrust of our&nbsp;

01:08:06.000 --> 01:08:12.960
YouTube channel as well. But I&nbsp;
wonder, now that you're retired,&nbsp;

01:08:14.320 --> 01:08:24.240
would you say that your emphasis is to share with&nbsp;
people what you learned long ago taking LSD? Or&nbsp;

01:08:24.240 --> 01:08:30.400
is it more that your emphasis is&nbsp;
to help save humanity from itself?&nbsp;

01:08:30.400 --> 01:08:34.640
Well, we haven't touched yet on what's&nbsp;
happening to humanity as a whole, but&nbsp;

01:08:34.640 --> 01:08:40.480
yeah, I guess first it took me a long time. I&nbsp;
really try to be candid in the book. The last&nbsp;

01:08:40.480 --> 01:08:46.560
chapter of the book is called Coming Off the&nbsp;
Mountain, and that was the longest chapter to&nbsp;

01:08:46.560 --> 01:08:52.880
write. It took me a year to write that chapter&nbsp;
because I had to really come to terms with&nbsp;

01:08:52.880 --> 01:09:01.200
what happened when I stopped my sessions. I&nbsp;
thought I was carefully attending to integration&nbsp;

01:09:01.200 --> 01:09:07.520
all the way up the mountain, really trying&nbsp;
to live the values that I had been shown,&nbsp;

01:09:07.520 --> 01:09:12.560
trying to maintain other forms of spiritual&nbsp;
practice. And I thought that when it was time&nbsp;

01:09:12.560 --> 01:09:20.800
to stop, that I would simply be able to withdraw&nbsp;
and hold on to those gems and let them nourish me.&nbsp;

01:09:20.800 --> 01:09:24.880
But what I found was that I had&nbsp;
entered so deeply so many times&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:09:24.880 --> 01:09:33.120
into the crystalline body of divinity
that I began to experience an existential&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:09:33.120 --> 01:09:41.680
kind of sadness. I knew I had to stop. My body was
telling me, my mind was telling me I had to stop.&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:09:43.440 --> 01:09:49.040
And I knew I would never enter into these states
again as deeply until I died.&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:09:50.000 --> 01:09:57.680
You can't enter these states simply by meditating
very firmly, not these radical states. And the&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:09:57.680 --> 01:10:04.880
sadness of not being able to enter into communion
with my beloved for years was very hard at first.&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:10:04.880 --> 01:10:13.360
It took me a long time. It took me about 10 years
to really become committed to living on this&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:10:13.360 --> 01:10:19.760
planet again with feet solidly grounded,
which is another reason why I wouldn't&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:10:19.760 --> 01:10:26.400
encourage people to do what I did,
because I knew that somewhere along the line&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:10:26.400 --> 01:10:31.920
I had made a mistake, and I didn't know where
that mistake was. And I turned to examine my&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:10:31.920 --> 01:10:37.760
history to find out where the mistake was.
And I began to realize that I had lost&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:10:37.760 --> 01:10:40.880
the balance, the critical&nbsp;
balance between transcendence&nbsp;

01:10:40.880 --> 01:10:48.560
and eminence, between leaving time space and&nbsp;
going into the infinite and then being grounded&nbsp;

01:10:48.560 --> 01:10:54.400
in time space, which is the other important&nbsp;
truth. And I was basically overextended,&nbsp;

01:10:54.400 --> 01:11:01.040
I was spiritually overextended, and I made&nbsp;
a conscious decision to ground myself inside&nbsp;

01:11:01.040 --> 01:11:08.000
the planet in my life. But the second reason that&nbsp;
it was hard is because I wasn't allowed to talk&nbsp;

01:11:08.000 --> 01:11:13.280
about my experiences. I'm a teacher. I love to&nbsp;
share information. I wasn't allowed to share&nbsp;

01:11:13.280 --> 01:11:19.520
that information. So writing LSD in the Mind&nbsp;
of the Universe was the beginning of healing&nbsp;

01:11:19.520 --> 01:11:25.520
that wound of silence so that I could take the&nbsp;
two, I'd split my life in two hearts. I was a&nbsp;

01:11:25.520 --> 01:11:31.200
professor and I was a psychonaut, but finally&nbsp;
being honest about my experiences allowed those&nbsp;

01:11:31.200 --> 01:11:38.160
to come back together, and I began to be whole&nbsp;
within myself. And that process continues.&nbsp;

01:11:38.160 --> 01:11:44.400
So what I've been asking myself and see the years&nbsp;
since LSD in the Mind of the Universe has been&nbsp;

01:11:44.400 --> 01:11:51.920
published is, how can I be useful? How can I make&nbsp;
this unusual journey which I've taken useful to&nbsp;

01:11:51.920 --> 01:11:56.400
other people without, I'm&nbsp;
not teaching them to go into&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:11:56.400 --> 01:12:02.080
these states, I'm not holding their hand while
they go into these states. That's other people's&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:12:02.080 --> 01:12:07.600
work, the holotropic breathwork people, the other
psychedelic therapists, that's what they're doing.&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:12:07.600 --> 01:12:16.240
I'm basically, first I don't really have an
agenda. I'm comfortable just being writing my&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:12:16.240 --> 01:12:21.680
life out as it is. I don't have any felt need to
accomplish anything or to do anything, but I'd&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:12:21.680 --> 01:12:28.640
like to be helpful. I'd like to be useful. And I
think that means convening circles of conversation&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:12:28.640 --> 01:12:36.240
around the themes of the book, drawing people in
inviting people in who have psychedelic&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:12:36.240 --> 01:12:42.560
experiences, drawing people in who have spiritual
experiences without any psychedelics involved, so&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:12:42.560 --> 01:12:51.680
that we can together process the deeper mysteries
of life that psychedelics can reveal. And slowly&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:12:51.680 --> 01:12:57.360
that seems to be taking shape. I basically go
where I'm invited. I don't really seek&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:12:57.360 --> 01:13:01.600
invitations, but if people want&nbsp;
to have conversations about&nbsp;

01:13:01.600 --> 01:13:08.160
these things, I'm happy to go there. Well,&nbsp;
you're certainly invited to come back here.&nbsp;

01:13:08.160 --> 01:13:14.960
Yeah, now we go to actually one of the most&nbsp;
surprising aspects of the journey was insights&nbsp;

01:13:14.960 --> 01:13:20.640
into where humanity is and its spiritual evolution&nbsp;
and where it's going, which I didn't even, I had&nbsp;

01:13:20.640 --> 01:13:26.240
no idea that this was possible when I went into&nbsp;
this work, but it actually became one of the&nbsp;

01:13:26.240 --> 01:13:34.000
dominant motifs of the work. And I kept on having&nbsp;
visions over a six-year period of humanity coming&nbsp;

01:13:34.000 --> 01:13:40.560
to a turning point, coming to a before and after,&nbsp;
history, epic-making turning point, that we were&nbsp;

01:13:40.560 --> 01:13:49.200
going into a time of profound spiritual awakening,&nbsp;
profound spiritual breakthrough. And this went on&nbsp;

01:13:49.200 --> 01:13:56.000
for years, but it never showed me how we were&nbsp;
going to get there. I looked around and I didn't&nbsp;

01:13:56.000 --> 01:14:01.520
see us, I saw us heading to the mall and to&nbsp;
the football stadium as much as to a spiritual&nbsp;

01:14:01.520 --> 01:14:09.520
breakthrough. And then I had that experience in&nbsp;
one session, which took me deeply into the future,&nbsp;

01:14:09.520 --> 01:14:15.520
not as Chris Bache, but again dissolved into the&nbsp;
collective psyche and gave me the experience of&nbsp;

01:14:15.520 --> 01:14:22.320
the death and rebirth that humanity is coming&nbsp;
into, a time of profound deconstruction, a time&nbsp;

01:14:22.320 --> 01:14:30.080
of loss of control, a time of great existential&nbsp;
suffering, which is global, not national or&nbsp;

01:14:30.080 --> 01:14:37.120
individual, it's just global, a time which the&nbsp;
suffering will be so severe, at least in my&nbsp;

01:14:37.120 --> 01:14:43.840
experience, that we might think it will be an&nbsp;
extinction event, that we are coming to the end&nbsp;

01:14:43.840 --> 01:14:50.320
of the line for humanity on this planet. We've so&nbsp;
overdrawn and overtaxed our systems, but at least&nbsp;

01:14:50.320 --> 01:14:56.240
in my experiences, I was shown that we come&nbsp;
through this experience. We're reduced in number,&nbsp;

01:14:56.240 --> 01:15:01.840
but we come through this experience and something&nbsp;
about the depth of suffering that we encounter&nbsp;

01:15:01.840 --> 01:15:09.120
opens us up at the deepest level of our being.&nbsp;
It opens our heart and it opens our mind.&nbsp;

01:15:09.120 --> 01:15:12.080
And there were a lot of teachings around&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:15:12.080 --> 01:15:15.200
non-linear systems and what&nbsp;
happens when the collective&nbsp;

01:15:15.200 --> 01:15:21.040
psyche, the collective unconscious is activated&nbsp;
at such a deep level, but that in this period of&nbsp;

01:15:21.040 --> 01:15:28.000
history, we are giving birth to the next iteration&nbsp;
of humanity. And I think it has to do with the&nbsp;

01:15:28.000 --> 01:15:33.520
birth of the diamond soul. I think we are coming,&nbsp;
we can no longer afford to live in a planet which&nbsp;

01:15:33.520 --> 01:15:40.720
is being run by egos, even well-intentioned&nbsp;
egos. We need to grow up if we're really going to&nbsp;

01:15:40.720 --> 01:15:47.920
survive as a species. And I think growing up&nbsp;
means growing into the great age which has been&nbsp;

01:15:47.920 --> 01:15:53.680
gestating within us for thousands and thousands&nbsp;
of years, letting that age express itself and&nbsp;

01:15:53.680 --> 01:16:01.280
taking us forward. So I think that we are coming&nbsp;
into a time of intense suffering, intense labor,&nbsp;

